七双手，两班倒，每天给医生护士送500杯免费咖啡……武汉一家咖啡店最近成了“网红”。
Seven hands, two shifts, daily delivery of 500 cups of free coffee to doctors and nurses... Wuhan coffee shop has recently become "net red."
总台记者走进这家咖啡店，探访暖心咖啡背后的故事。
The front desk reporter walks into the coffee shop to see the story behind the warm coffee.
每天分两次给医护人员送咖啡这家名叫Wakanda的咖啡店从武汉实行交通管制起，开始为抗“疫”一线的医护人员送免费咖啡，一直坚持到今天。
The Wakanda cafe, which controls traffic from Wuhan, began delivering free coffee to health-care workers fighting the plague until today.
当记者来到咖啡厅时，店里的工作人员正在准备上午的供货。
When the reporter came to the coffee shop, the shop staff was preparing for the morning delivery.
谈到送咖啡的初衷，咖啡店负责人李飞说，“武汉实行交通管制后，有医护人员来店里买咖啡，和他们聊天后得知现在医院的工作量特别大，医护人员工作非常辛苦。
After Wuhan imposed traffic control regulations, some medical workers came to the store to buy coffee and chatted with them. After talking to them, they learned that the workload of the hospital was particularly heavy and the staff worked very hard.
受疫情影响，咖啡店目前无法正常营业，不如做点公益。
Due to the epidemic, the coffee shop is unable to operate normally, so we should do something for the public.
”为避免“给医院带来麻烦”，咖啡店每天分两次给医护人员送咖啡，一次在中午就餐时间，另一次在下午医护人员换班的时候。
To avoid "bothering the hospital," the coffee shop serves coffee to staff twice a day, once at noon and once in the afternoon when staff change jobs.
咖啡店把咖啡送到医院的志愿者中转站，再由志愿者用中转车统一送到医护人员手中。
The coffee shop sends the coffee to the volunteer transit station in the hospital, where the volunteers transfer the coffee to the medical staff.
目前店里有7名员工，他们之中既有武汉本地人，也有外地人，还有一名来自伊朗的咖啡师西纳。
The store currently employs seven people, including Wuhan natives and outsiders, as well as an Iranian coffee maker named Sinah.
他们每天从早上9点多开始做准备工作，需要在两三个小时内完成两三百杯咖啡的制作。
They start their preparation at more than 9 a. m., and need to make two or three hundred cups of coffee in two or three hours.
西纳：我现在也认为自己是中国人，我会留在这里。
Sina: I think I'm Chinese now, too. I'll stay here.
和中国人一样，这里现在就是我的家，我会和中国人在一起。
Like the Chinese, this is my home now, and I will be with the Chinese.
网友实力应援 “云买单”为武汉医护人员买咖啡近日，网友得知了咖啡店的善举，也纷纷通过手机App进行“云买单”，实力应援这样的爱心举动。
Recently, netizens learned the good action of the coffee shop. They also paid for it through their mobile phone App, and their strength should help this kind of loving act.
据李飞介绍，短短3天内，参与“云买单”的网友就达1万多人。
In just three days, more than 10,000 netizens took part in the "cloud bill," according to Li.
本来，咖啡店的员工觉得这是件很小的事，但网友的加入令他们感到了肩上承担的分量，决定将这件事当作“一份事业，一种任务”来完成。
The coffee shop staff thought it was a small matter, but they felt the weight was on their shoulders and decided to do it as "a career, a task."
为了鼓励辛苦工作的医护人员，擅长美术的店员还在每个咖啡杯上手写“向您致敬”“您最可爱”“感恩有您”等祝福语。
To encourage hard-working health-care workers, art-savvy salespeople write "Hail to You" and "Thank You" on each coffee cup.
有网友参与“云买单”后，店员便将参与者的名字写在每句祝福语的下面，将网友们的爱心和支持一并送给医护人员。
Some netizens take part in the "cloud pay the bill", the clerk then writes the participant's name in each toast below, sends the netizen's love and the support together to the medical personnel.
不少网友知道咖啡店的做法后颇受感动，立刻下单“云品尝”咖啡，请医护人员喝咖啡！还有网友表示，疫情结束，要去咖啡店打卡！来源：央视新闻综合中国之声推荐阅读点击大图|1晚获73万元打赏，1夜120万人“云蹦迪”，虚拟线上娱乐，真能“蹦”起来？点击大图|竟然开始“斗舞”了，说方舱医院是“集中营”的外国黑媒傻了。
Many netizens, aware of the coffee shop's practices, were immediately moved to order "Cloud taste" coffee and ask medical staff to drink coffee! Others say the epidemic ended with a $730,000 reward for late-night visits, 1.2 million "Cloud Jumping" and virtual online entertainment.
